headline: Detroit's iconic Renaissance Center could see 2 towers razed in $1.6B redevelopment plan
summary: Two towers at Detroit's iconic Renaissance Center would be razed and the complex converted to a mix of housing and offices under an ambitious $1.6 billion plan announced Monday.  The complex, which next year will lose the headquarters of owner General Motors Co., is the symbol of Detroit, with aerial views often shown on television sports broadcasts.  GM decided last spring to leave what's locally known as the “RenCen” for a more modern building being constructed downtown.

headline: Formula One owner Liberty Media shares up after GM entry
summary: Investing.com - Formula One owner Liberty Media Formula One Corp A (NASDAQ:FWONA) shares were up more than 4% at $80. The company has reached an agreement in principle with General Motors (NYSE:GM) to support bringing GM/Cadillac as the 11th team to the Formula 1 grid in 2026.

headline: Formula 1 expands grid to add General Motors' Cadillac brand and new American team for 2026 season
summary: Formula 1 on Monday at last said it will expand its grid in 2026 to make room for an American team that is partnered with General Motors.  "This is a global stage for us to demonstrate GM’s engineering expertise and technology leadership at an entirely new level.”  The approval ends years of wrangling that launched a U.S. Justice Department investigation into why Colorado-based Liberty Media, the commercial rights holder of F1, would not approve the team initially started by Michael Andretti.
